Sentence: The smaller T c reduction (0.2 K) of the 2 GPa pressure-compacted wire with the Al+Al 2 O 3 sheath compared to the wire with the GlidCop sheath (0.6 K) chould be explained by a smaller residual strain induced inside the softer Al+Al 2 O 3 sheath.
The T c decrease by applied isostatic pressure is attributed to a residual strain acting on MgB 2 formation, where the residual strain increases with the degree of applied pressure.
